🧑🏻‍💻 Social Media Strategist, Fitness Addict, Tech Nerd, & Photographer
🏆 Founder of @Clonefluence & @Clonedgg
🗞 @Forbes Contributor

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Justin Grome on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and beach.

node.text:
New @forbes article is up today titled “Four Tips For Making Yourself More Marketable As An Aspiring Musician.”

Been trying to be as versatile as possible with my writing to help as many people with information that’s needed to succeed in multiple fields. I’ve covered networking, gaming, Twitch streaming, marketing, and the music industry so far!

If you haven’t read my articles, make sure you go to my Forbes highlight on my profile and you can click any of the links you’d like. Now is the perfect time to catch up!

Make sure you tag your fellow musicians or friends if you want to see them grow in the future!🤘🏻

node.text:
Happy 4th of July!🥳🎊
If you’re outside of the US, don’t forget to enjoy your Sunday and do something you enjoy today, you deserve it!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Justin Grome in Clonefluence. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Blessed to achieve one of my lifetime goals of 1m followers. Have some really great things in store for the coming months! Super excited to show you all. Thank you for sticking by me and supporting @Clonefluence, @Clonedgg, and I throughout the years!🎉

Also, been feeling great lately about my fitness journey! Nutrition and fitness is my hobby, but also a lifestyle at this point! Among the social media strategizing and writing I do, I would always lift but never watch my diet. I love to feel good and do what makes me feel good, only until recently did I realize my old habits got out of hand during college. Dieting and cutting does a lot more than you ever think it could by just watching some key macros. Body fat is down to about 10% from 18%, time to keep improving! You can scroll down my page and progressively see me thinning out with every picture as you get to the top!🏋🏻

Cheers to my lifetime follower goal of 1m and my fitness journey!🥂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Justin Grome in Clonefluence with @hxylstxrm. May be an image of 1 person, standing and suit.

node.text:
A lot of people have been asking me “How do you stay motivated?”

The answer will be in my next @forbes article! Stay tuned.

Thank you all for giving me such great input on what I should write about next. I want to answer as many of your questions as possible in a lengthy form.

node.text:
On Monday morning I got a call from a director of @forbes saying I got accepted into their Business Council with some of the most authoritative businessmen and women in the world.

It’s truly an honor to say that I made it onto Forbes in not just an article, but a member of their council at the age of 22.

Keep your head up if you feel like things aren’t working out for you now. I would personally like to let you know that anything is possible if you put your mind to it.

Thank you to everyone who supported me along the way!😁
